There is some workaround in the given link, but it's a cipher to me :)

Can I have a question, why is the "last resort" branch even there? I thought PHP's unlink() works on Win as well.

So what about this?
```php
try {
    return unlink($path);
} catch (ErrorException $e) {
    // last resort measure for Windows
    if (file_exists($path)) {
        $lines = [];
        exec('DEL /F/Q ' . escapeshellarg($path), $lines, $deleteError);

        return !file_exists($path);
